description.1: Cable and the Avengers may have stemmed the coming of Apocalypse, but where did Cable disappear to in the battle’s aftermath? The EPIC CONCLUSION to Sign of the End Times!
description.5: X-FORCE recovers after a titantic clash with the new HELLIONS and the ARMAGEDDON MAN and return home to San Francisco. But who will leave the team? Will there be an all-new X-Force after this?
description.9: Iron Man engages Fin Fang Foom in a heated battle. How will Tony uproot an evil as ancient as the wrathful Foom?
description.10: Anakin joins Queen Amidala in the planning of the Battle for Naboo. Will the Jedi Force prove enough against the power of the Dark Sith?
description.11: There will soon come a day when the future of'the galaxy'hinges on the fate of one boy, though he does not yet know it. Growing up on the desert world'Tatooine,'Anakin Skywalker'never thought he would venture beyond the small life he has. Simple, boyhood pursuits seem like the only things he should be concerned with. But destiny has other things in mind.
description.12: Check out the comic book adpatation of Anakin's podrace victory over Queen Amidala! In the third chapter of Phantom Menace, Anakin makes peace with his destiny- and Boss Nass and the Gungans!
description.13: The insidious Darth Vader has arrived on the planet Jazbina, with devastating consequences! Having learned that the pilot who destroyed the Death Star was none other than his own son, he comes face to face for the first time with Luke Skywalker! The planet's populace stands ready to assist Luke against the evil Dark Lord, but with an Imperial Cruiser over their heads, are they willing to pay the price for defying Vader?
description.14: As Ki races to save his daughter from the clutches of the vile gangster Jabba the Hutt, he inadvertently discovers that the Hutt crime lord is secretly procuring munitions for a war fleet massing in orbit above Tatooine. Suddenly, Ki's problems on his homeworld of Cerea seem very small indeed!'
description.15: The second installment in young Anakin Skywalker's awakening to the Force!
description.22: GALACTUS HAS COME! The Devourer of Worlds has his sights set on Prison World, which means only one thing: Wolverine is about to become cosmic lunch!
description.23: Adapted for comics by'Henry Gilroy'from an original screenplay by master movie maker'George Lucas, and artfully illustrated by'Rodolfo Damaggio'and comics legend'Al Williamson, make sure you catch this legendary series that's sure to please Star Wars'fans of all ages.
description.24: The precursor comic to Phantom Menace, the first chapter in the life of Anakin Skywalker! Meet the nine year old boy who will come to be ruler of the Dark Force.
description.29: It's voting day in the city of Attilan.
description.30: Heavy is The Head That Wears the Crown. Magneto, mutant radical and leader of a charged rebellion, emerges as the new sovereign of Genosha, an independent mutant state. But a civil war has erupted between the Magistrates and mutates...leaving Magneto in a diplomatic bind! Quicksilver and Rogue guest-star!
description.33: T'Challa held captive by Manuel Ramos! But when Panther escapes, he finds himself prey to the villain who last bested him- Kraven the Hunter! A game of cat and mouse turns fatal.
description.34: Captain America must decide if one man's life is worth the fate of the world! The Red Skull battle continues!
description.35: When two villains join forces against Spider-Girl, Spider-Girl suddenly finds herself joining forces with...her dad?
description.36: The X-Men mourn a fallen friend while Wolverine prepares to assasinate Magneto.
description.37: The townspeople have rallied against Hulk and try to drive him out. Surely they'll be able to tell the Hulk what to do...
description.40: Trapped in the Negative Zone - and framed as super-criminals, to boot! Can the FF find their way home before the Negative Zone enforcer Lockdown catches up with them, and puts them behind negative bars forever?
description.43: It's a deciding showdown between X-Force and the New Hellions! Plus, can the team stop the Armageddon Man from bringing a nuclear winter to California?
description.45: Will Fin Fang Foom rise again? The ancient dragon plots his return using a human pawn. Happy celebrates his new role at the Maria Stark Foundation.
description.47: Guest-starring Earth’s Mightiest Heroes! Cable gets an assist from the AVENGERS in his attempt to save the world the Harbinger of Apocalypse!
description.48: Four, count 'em, four Spider-Women! Mattie Franklin encounters a sinister new Spider-Woman who's creating a bad rep for spider-heroes at large. Spider-Woman Jessica Drew and former Spider-Woman Julia Carpenter guest-star!
description.52: The stage is set for the confrontation that will rock'the galaxy!'Boba Fett has dispatched'Darth Vader's thugs with ease, but now the'Dark Lord himself has arrived to claim the strange little box in Fett's possession. Dark Lord or not, Fett isn't about to give up the prize. After all, he's got a reputation to uphold!
description.53: It all comes together in this issue: Young Luke Skywalker hunts for the missing princess of Jazbina, oblivious to the real reason she has disappeared! The Rebel pilot Jal races to find Luke in the hope that the Empire hasn't found the Alliance's hero first! And Darth Vader prepares to land on Jazbina... Will the Dark Lord finally have his long-lost son in his clutches? Find out in this never-before-revealed sequel to the first Star Wars film!
description.54: High above the desert sands of'Tatooine, a battle of life and death is taking place! On a freighter loaded with bloodthirsty beasts, lone'Jedi'Ki-Adi-Mundi must fight his way to his daughter, trapped in a malfunctioning escape pod with the merciless, but just as helpless, criminal'Ephant Mon. Only Ki can save them, but the only way to save them may be to let Ephant Mon escape with Ki's daughter!
description.56: As the'Baron's forces lay waste to the'Interim Council's'guarded planet,Sinn'and'Kanos'hurtle toward the heat of the'battle'in an attempt to thwart the escape of'Feena D'Asta's'clone. But will they arrive in time? And what happened to the treacherous'Grappa'the'Hutt? Has he escaped unscathed from all the trouble that he raised?
description.63: Wolverine vs. the STARJAMMERS! Plus: The secret origin - and shocking secret - of Prison World!
description.65: King Black Bolt struggles with what to do about the humans outside his city. To destroy them with but a word...or not? That is the question.
description.68: At a state dinner in New York, Kraven the Hunter attacks Black Panther...with a hungry lion in tow! Plus, conflict over the Dora Milaje's true function.
description.69: Red Skull has conquered the world. Captain America is the only one that can save the day. Will he be able to beat the almighty Red Skull?
description.71: The X-Men battle the Acolytes while Joseph and Astra confront Magneto.
description.72: Hulk smashes his way into a new adventure! Can anything contain the Hulk's rage?
description.73: Joseph makes the ultimate sacrifice to save humanity.
description.75: Flung into the future, the FF finds themselves up against the Kree's mightiest warriors...the Avengers!?
description.79: The mystery behind Mainframe is finally revealed as he meets the evil Ion Man for the first time...
description.80: As the New Hellions problem gets bigger, an even bigger wrench is thrown into the works as the Armageddon Man threatens a mass destruction event!
description.82: Nitro targets Tony Stark at a public opening...and Iron Man answers the call! Tony unveils his newly modified armor.
description.83: Attack of the Trapster! Spider-Man lends some web-shooting hands to the Fantastic Four during their latest battle with the Frightful Four. Plus, an assassination plot against Senator Ward!
description.85: It is the End of Times! Cable vs. Apocalypse, with the fate of humankind at stake.
description.89: Boba Fett'has finally caught up to his quarry, but so have'Darth Vader's mercenary cronies. Stupid as they are, they're also cold-blooded killers, and they're not foolish enough to disobey the'Dark Lord of the Sith. But just in case they aren't good enough to take out the'bounty hunter, Darth Vader himself arrives to complete the mission!
description.90: Darth Vader has commissioned a network of spies and rogues to track down young Luke Skywalker, and one of them has struck paydirt in the form of Jal, the Rebel pilot who was forced to sit out the Battle of Yavin while Skywalker destroyed the Death Star and took all the glory. Drunk and miserable, Jal barely survives an Imperial attack and realizes that information he has casually shared might very well destroy Luke Skywalker, and perhaps the entire Rebel Alliance!
description.91: Sylvn'and the fugitives have taken flight from'Cerea, but their starship's cargo hold is fit to burst with a load of unstoppable alien beasts. Action was what the youngsters hoped to find in the space lanes beyond their provincial homeworld, but now they have more than they bargained for, and a trial back home to face the consequences of their actions is beginning to sound downright cozy!
description.93: It's revelation time, as the series begins to accelerate toward its thrilling conclusion. A hair-raising rescue attempt on the part of'Kir Kanos'goes afoul while the'Interim Council'finally collapses beneath its array of intrigues. And'Grappa'learns the meaning of "caught between a rock and a hard place."

0.text: The Green Goblin. The Green Goliath. And Spidey caught in the middle.

1.text: Cable and the Avengers may have stemmed the coming of Apocalypse, but where did Cable disappear to in the battle’s aftermath? The EPIC CONCLUSION to Sign of the End Times!

2.text: Matt attends the funeral of Karen Page. Foggy's name is cleared and he's released from prison. And the fate of the mysterious child is revealed... Featuring, Spider-Man!
Matt attends the funeral of Karen Page. Foggy's name is cleared and he's released from prison. And the fate of the mysterious child is revealed... Featuring, Spider-Man!

3.text: A team of Avengers pursues the Wrecking Crew, which has abducted Photon to another realm, while the rest of Earth's Mightiest Heroes must save Carol Danvers from the Doomsday Man.

4.text: Thunderstrike and Blacklight vs. the Soldiers of the Serpent!

6.text: In the aftermath to Magneto’s rise to power, Professor X pushes his team to the brink. Is this the end of the dream?

8.text: In order to defeat the Dark Gods, Thor has allied himself with the Destroyer! Can Thor and one of the most powerful weapons in reality take down Asgard's divine aggressors?

16.text: From the wreckage of Onslaught comes an all-new menace.  Are the Avengers up to the task of stopping them?

17.text: When Wrecking Crew begins destroying New Orleans in search of Photon, the Avengers come to the rescue!

19.text: Deadpool is set up by Alestair to run into his deceased wife Mercedes in the streets of Atlanta while she's being hunted by Bullseye!

21.text: The Avengers assemble for one last crack at Immortus to save forever!
The Avengers assemble for one last crack at Immortus to save forever!

22.text: GALACTUS HAS COME! The Devourer of Worlds has his sights set on Prison World, which means only one thing: Wolverine is about to become cosmic lunch!

25.text: Back in de Big Easy! Our hero returns to his home turf at the request of Tante Mattie and his father Jean-Luc LeBeau. An ancient, vampiric evil has reemerged, and is threatening the lives of children sold to the Antiquary! Blade makes a painSTAKING appearance!

26.text: Sam Wilson steps in for Captain America, who is believed to be dead. It’s up to Falcon to protect Harlem from racial riots!

27.text: The stunning conclusion to Doctor Strange's Marvel Knights debut!

28.text: Learn the final fate of the Fantastic Four in their final battle against Doctor Doom and Namor!

31.text: Spider-Man is no stranger to girl problems… but this may be a new extreme. One of the girls from his past now wants him DEAD!

32.text: Can Spider-Man alone challenge an extremely motivated Silver Surfer? As if that wasn't enough, Spidey faces another daunting enemy, the ever powerful Psycho-Man.

38.text: The mutants…mutated! The X-Men have their powers amplified to freakish levels when they are thrown into a dimension that refutes the laws of physics!

39.text: LOCKDOWN For the good of the team, he gave up his liberty to atone for his sins. Now MACH-1 is back in prison, surrounded by the super-villains who used to be his peers- and who now want him dead! Will a prison break gone awry restore his freedom- or just give the Rhino, Boomerang and Whirlwind the chance to finish him off?

41.text: The showdown between Daredevil and the man behind Karen's death, the appearance of the Messiah baby, and all that has befallen Matt Murdock is here! Two shall fight...one shall live.
The showdown between Daredevil and the man behind Karen's death, the appearance of the Messiah baby, and all that has befallen Matt Murdock is here! Two shall fight...one shall live.

42.text: While Ant-Man and Stinger assist Mainframe, the rest of the team finds out where Scarlet Witch has been hiding!

44.text: With Mjolnir broken, Thor has transformed back into Jake. In a desperate attempt to rescue his comrades, Thor must make a deal with the most unlikely enemy!

46.text: The Goblin Queen's corruption extends from The Six to the U.S. Government, the Sentinel Army and even Reed Richards! Havok fights alone!

47.text: Guest-starring Earth’s Mightiest Heroes! Cable gets an assist from the AVENGERS in his attempt to save the world the Harbinger of Apocalypse!

49.text: Discover the origins of Vulture, Sandman, and the Lizard!

50.text: Will Spidey see through the illusion that is Mysterio?

55.text: Ensnared in a game of international intrigue! Gambit runs afoul of a madcap crew known as A.S.K.E.W, while tracking mutant messenger, Courier. Introducing the Mengo Brothers, professional thugs of the Pig! Plus, what’s all this talk about a mind-controlling gas?

57.text: Iron Man and the Avengers track Lord Templar to a mysterious religious organization known as the Triune Understanding.  Will former ally Triathlon aid the Avengers or stand by his benefactors in the Triune?

60.text: The prescription for Wade's mental problems? A forced fight with Wolverine! It's the breakthrough of the century as Deadpool realizes the phantom lady of his hallucinations is...his wife?

62.text: Past Imperfect...Future Tense.  Can the Avengers scattered across forever stop Immortus' time wave before everything is changed?
Past Imperfect...Future Tense.  Can the Avengers scattered across forever stop Immortus' time wave before everything is changed?

63.text: Wolverine vs. the STARJAMMERS! Plus: The secret origin - and shocking secret - of Prison World!

64.text: In a future Marvel Universe where Plague X has given everyone powers, Captain America is the last human alive.  Can he and his allies stop the new Red Skull?
In a future Marvel Universe where Plague X has given everyone powers, Captain America is the last human alive. Can he and his allies stop the new Red Skull?

66.text: Spidey’s team-up with the X-Men continues! This time our favorite web-slinger works with Marrow to uncover a mystery of disappearing New Yorkers.

67.text: We discover why the Silver Surfer was ready and able to pick a fight against humankind, but it didn't end up happening. Can Spider-Man stop the Surfer's crazy streak?

74.text: THE SCOOP: It's the culmination of the ongoing plot threads since issue #18 as Hawkeye and the Thunderbolts and their former namesakes, the Masters of Evil, square off in a double-sized slobberknocker! THE STORY: They've bullied and bruised the Thunderbolts; now the new Masters of Evil are threatening the safety of the entire world! And who are the only ones in a position to stop them? You guessed it: their sworn enemies, the outnumbered and outgunned T-bolts! Plus: The Crimson Cowl- unmasked!

76.text: The terrorist group Sons of the Serpent is now going by Sons of the Shield…complete with fake endorsement from Captain America! Falcon steps in to knock some heads.

77.text: The trail of mystic crimes comes together at last! Stephen Strange once again comes face to face with his oldest and deadliest foe, as the climax of "THE FLIGHT OF BONES" begins!

78.text: Karen's death has taken its toll on Matt Murdock. As he contemplates ending his life, he comes to the realization that he must persevere...he must fight. The mastermind behind this whole ordeal is revealed here!

Karen's death has taken its toll on Matt Murdock. As he contemplates ending his life, he comes to the realization that he must persevere...he must fight. The mastermind behind this whole ordeal is revealed here!

81.text: With the highest ranking members of the Norse Pantheon imprisoned by the Dark Gods, Thor is the only Asgardian capable of saving his brethren and Asgard itself!

84.text: Can Spidey cure the Lizard? And can he turn off the lights on Electro?

85.text: It is the End of Times! Cable vs. Apocalypse, with the fate of humankind at stake.

86.text: Mister Sinister seeks to tap into Cable’s unlocked potential -- as the genetically engineered destroyer of Apocalypse! But will Cable fulfill his role as a vessel of death? And with Cable’s powers dwindling, will such a feat even be possible?

87.text: The Six become The Five when the Goblin Queen corrupts the team. Can Havok escape to recruit enough firepower to take on his former teammates?

92.text: The fur flies quite literally as Wolverine and Deadpool take on a vengeful werewolf! But who’s hunting who? In this thrill-inducing annual, Wolverine: plays a super hero poker game, nearly destroys Nick Fury’s flying car, and disturbs a ninja ritual involving dragons! All while picking up a six-pack of beer!

95.text: Beast returns to catch up with his old pal Wonder Man, with Vision and Scarlet Witch joining them for a night on the town. Surely nothing will interrupt these Avengers' quiet evening...

96.text: Terrorist Flag-Smasher is leaving a trail of blood in the New York City tunnels. But to what end? The entire team investigates, including a reluctant Marrow, still distrustful of her new, mutant family. Shadowcat flies into a frenzy. Marrow does some very questionable things.

98.text: Asgard has disappeared! Back on Earth, Thor battles the lethal android known as Replicus!

99.text: Deadpool takes on an Arabian rescuing/kidnapping and a new assassination assignment, which begins a cycle of madness for resulting in Wade seeking counseling. His treatment provider? Why, it's Dr. Bong!
